    "content": "**Geopolitiks Snacks** - May 20, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🚢 Hormuz became permissioned infrastructure\n\nThe world's energy choke point is now apparently a managed queue, because shipping lanes needed an access-control layer.\n\n- **The transit:** Al Jazeera says Iran's IRGC claimed it coordinated 26 vessels through Hormuz in 24 hours, with passage requiring IRGC Navy permission.\n- **The squeeze:** about one-fifth of global energy exports used to move through the strait before the February 28 U.S.-Israel war on Iran and Tehran's blockade.\n- **The spillover:** FAO warned the blockage could trigger a global food price crisis within six to 12 months as energy and fertilizer costs spread.\n\n*Diplomacy has entered the logistics dashboard.*\n\n**Sources:** [Al Jazeera](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/5/20/iran-says-it-coordinated-crossing-of-26-vessels-out-of-strait-of-hormuz) | [FAO](https://www.fao.org/newsroom/detail/fao--protracted-strait-of-hormuz-crisis-could-turn-into-global-agrifood-catastrophe/en)\n\n---\n\n## 🧯 The Senate found the war switch\n\nCongress has rediscovered Article I after 80 days, which is late but still a calendar entry.\n\n- **The vote:** Reuters says the Senate advanced Tim Kaine's Iran war-powers resolution 50-47 on May 19, with four Republicans joining nearly all Democrats.\n- **The target:** the measure would end the Iran war unless Trump gets congressional authorization, though it still faces the House and likely veto math.\n- **The clock:** the conflict began February 28, and Trump declared on May 1 that the ceasefire had \"terminated\" hostilities while U.S. blockades and strikes continued.\n\n*Procedural rebellion: the least cinematic branch of war policy.*\n\n**Sources:** [Reuters via Investing.com](https://www.investing.com/news/world-news/us-senate-advances-measure-curbing-trumps-iran-war-powers-4699898) | [AP](https://apnews.com/article/fe89d2df981a79ac816722d0115d3080)\n\n---\n\n## 🛢️ Xi and Putin renewed the friendship warranty\n\nBeijing hosted the alliance maintenance session, complete with treaty paperwork and energy subtext.\n\n- **The summit:** AP says Xi Jinping and Vladimir Putin met in Beijing on May 20, oversaw more than 40 cooperation agreements and extended their 2001 friendship treaty.\n- **The fuel:** Putin said energy cooperation drives the relationship; China is Russia's top trading partner and top customer for Russian oil and gas.\n- **The limit:** AP noted no visible progress on the Power of Siberia 2 pipeline, the big gas export prize Moscow keeps pushing.\n\n*The partnership is historic. The pipeline still wants signatures.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/china-russia-putin-xi-5b7304bc1604cbb7135cb96f217b8b3e) | [Al Jazeera](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/5/20/multipolar-world-what-xi-and-putin-announced-after-beijing-summit)\n\n---\n\n## 🛰️ Ukraine's strike spiral kept widening\n\nThe ceasefire that was supposed to cool things down has produced the familiar innovation: bigger barrages.\n\n- **The barrage:** AP reports Russia hit eight Ukrainian regions overnight, with Zelenskyy saying 524 attack drones and 22 ballistic and cruise missiles were launched.\n- **The damage:** local officials reported more than two dozen wounded civilians, including three children, with Dnipro and the surrounding region hit hardest.\n- **The reply:** AP says Ukraine's recent drone strikes inside Russia killed four people, while Defense Minister Mykhailo Fedorov announced Ukraine's first glide bomb.\n\n*Long-range escalation remains the only peace process with a production schedule.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/russia-ukraine-war-drone-missile-attacks-putin-cfdab5379fa9c68b9a494da7473445d7) | [Reuters via Investing.com](https://www.investing.com/news/world-news/russia-attacks-ukraines-danube-port-city-ukraine-launches-drones-towards-moscow-4697428)"
  }
]
